-- Noriega Is Sentenced to Seven Years in Prison by Paris Court, AP Reports
-- Heather Smith
-- 2010-07-07T12:29:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/noriega-is-sentenced-to-seven-years-in-prison-by-paris-court-ap-reports.html

          
          
             Former Panamanian President  Manuel Noriega  was sentenced by a Paris court to seven years in prison
for money laundering, Associated Press said today, citing the
court.  
 Noriega passed drug money through French bank accounts in
the 1980s, AP said. Calls by Bloomberg News to his lawyer for
comment were not immediately returned.  
